Itis with infinite concern the Committee has to

inform the Society of the death of its excellent co· adjutor, Dr D. Smith, who died, after a very short

illness, on the very day (22d May 1805) when the last of his labours in its service, the concluding sheet of this Appendix, issued from the press. The Committee has to sympathize with every lover of Celtic literature, on the loss of a scholar and anti- quarian, whose extent of knowledge, whose acute- ness, and whose industry, have seldom been equal- ed. assuming manners that accompanied them) which
